```sql
-- 1) upsert (handles new + changed orders atomically)
merge into sales.orders t
using staging.order_changes s on t.order_id = s.order_id
when matched then update set *
when not matched then insert *;

-- 2) compact small files + co-locate by the filter column for data skipping
optimize sales.orders zorder by (order_id);

-- 3) read a prior version (e.g. to compare or recover)
select * from sales.orders version as of (
  select max(version)-3 from (describe history sales.orders)
);
-- or simply: select * from sales.orders version as of 9;
```
The `MERGE` is the transactional upsert; `OPTIMIZE … ZORDER BY` compacts and clusters so future `where order_id = …` queries **skip files** via min/max stats; `VERSION AS OF` uses Delta **time travel** to read history (you can also `RESTORE TABLE … TO VERSION AS OF 9` to roll back).

